  "text": "Formulations containing surfactants with higher (>12) HLB values (e.g., T80 and Cr-El, hydrophilic in nature) exhibited good self-emulsifying properties compared to formulations containing surfactants with lower (<10) HLB values (e.g., span 20 and span 80, lipophilic in nature). These findings are matching with previously reported data which suggested that the required HLB value of a surfactant for developing suitable self-emulsifying formulation should preferably be around 10 or higher [CITATION_1] .",
